  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nCurrently you can only use `@TestSecurity` with `@QuarkusTest`. I believe that simplifying a security testing for users that use native executables would also be useful. In general, I understand that integration tests are likely to test integration with other software components like SSO, but we should not force that. It would be nice if user could have one test base that they can run with both QuarkusTest and QuarkusIntegrationTest.\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\nExpose test non-application endpoint that sets the identity instead of using Arc to propagate selected identity during integration testing.",
